# Final Mini-SoC Project

## Overview

This project is a custom educational Mini-SoC developed using Verilog/SystemVerilog to understand real SoC architecture, on-chip buses, protocol conversion, peripheral integration, and verification methodologies.

The design incrementally builds a complete SoC platform using industry-style modular development.

---

# Current Architecture

AXI Master TB
    ↓
AXI Interconnect
    ├── AXI SRAM
    └── AXI → APB Bridge
                    ↓
              APB Subsystem
         ├── GPIO Peripheral
         ├── UART Stub
         └── SPI Stub

---

# Supported Protocols

- AXI4-Lite
- APB3

---

# Key Features

- AXI4-Lite Master Testbench
- AXI Interconnect with address decoding
- AXI SRAM Slave
- AXI → APB Protocol Bridge
- APB Decoder
- GPIO Peripheral
- UART Stub Peripheral
- SPI Stub Peripheral
- Full-system simulation environment
- Structured debug logging
- Waveform debugging using DVE/VPD

